# browser, so libcurl headers must be present even though we only build the
# local editors.
               libcurl4-openssl-dev,
# BUILD_WITH_ALL pulls every script backend. Most are vendored submodules, but
# mruby builds with a host ruby + rake, so include them. If the first CI build
# complains about a missing tool, add it here (this is the file apt-get build-dep
# reads).
               ruby,
               rake
Standards-Version: 4.7.0
Homepage: https://tic80.com/

Package: tic80
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: TIC-80 tiny fantasy computer
 TIC-80 is a free and open source fantasy computer for making, playing and
 sharing tiny games, with built-in code/sprite/map/sfx/music editors.
 .
 This build links the system SDL2 and renders through SDLGPU on OpenGL ES 2.0
 / EGL (mesa + lima on the CHIP's Mali400), unlike upstream's rpi.deb which
 links the legacy Broadcom GLES blobs and will not load on the CHIP. TIC-80's
 native 240x136 framebuffer is an exact 2x of the 480x272 PocketCHIP panel.
